name: Hải Sản Tự Do
address: 149-151 Lê Đại Hành, Khuê Trung, Cẩm Lệ, Đà Nẵng 50708, Vietnam

reviews_list.content: Really delicious, good for meeting friends
Good service, fairly cheap, fresh seafood. Bonus is the airport is right behind you and you can do some planespotting while you are there
Ordered squid on the 100k menu, the bill was written by kg, 500k per kg, 250k per half kilo. If you dont drink beer, the waiter will look at you with half an eye.

Ive eaten at this restaurant twice, but the first time I didnt like it because of the kitchen. The second time was because I went with a group of friends. Every dish is spicy, so tell the chef to cook it and its okay to eat. There is a hot pot dish that looks simple but is expensive. The snails are almost as big as snails, so they are probably farmed snails. Its a bit scary to eat. The first time I ate snails, I bought 1/2kg and asked the kitchen to divide it into half, steamed and half roasted with salt. The chef said he couldnt do that, so in the end he had to buy 600gr and divide it into 2 dishes. The kitchen is weird, steaming is simple but theres nothing that cant be divided into different tasks.

The restaurant is too dirty. The spoon brought out for the customer had something on it like animal feces. I called the staff out and reminded them and asked for a new spoon. The staffs attitude was extremely bad. Didnt even say a word. He took the spoon in with one hand and brought out a PACK OF SPOONS AND PUT IT ON THE TABLE WITHOUT ANY ADDITIONAL WORDS. Didnt do anything to intimidate the customer. Maybe the restaurant has a lot of customers so they dont care about SERVICE AND HYGIENE.
